<chapter>
  <title><xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_Secure_Email"
  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"/> Module</title>

  <para role="TEXT"><xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_Secure_Email"
  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"/> provides an email-like
  communication channel between the customer and the bank, in both directions.
  It can be used for multiple purposes: correspondence, ad-hoc requests, new
  services that don't have a dedicated module, monthly advices sent by the
  bank, and so on.</para>

  <para role="TEXT">The <xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_Secure_Email"
  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"/> module of <xi:include
  href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_appli"
  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"/> enables you, on behalf of your
  company, to send messages to, and receive messages from, the bank.</para>

  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>Functions</title>

    <para role="TEXT">The menu for this module has the following groups of functions. Many
    are basically as described in the chapter
    <emphasis>Functions</emphasis>.</para>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><guimenuitem moreinfo="none">New Message</guimenuitem></term>

        <listitem>
          <para role="TEXT">Send a message to the bank.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>

    <para role="TEXT">The <guimenuitem role="bold">Message Inquiry</guimenuitem> and
    <guimenuitem role="bold">Message Maintenance</guimenuitem> parts of the
    menu are as described in chapter <emphasis>Functions</emphasis>. You use
    <guimenuitem role="bold">Message Inquiry</guimenuitem> to see messages
    from the bank. There is no <guimenuitem>Pending Message</guimenuitem>
    function.</para>
  </section>

  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>New Instruction</title>

    <para role="TEXT">This section describes the <guisubmenu>New Instruction</guisubmenu>
    part of the menu and the forms it uses.</para>

    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Secure Email Initiation Function</title>

      <para role="TEXT">This part of the menu contains several functions, providing
      different ways to send a message.</para>

      <section role="ITEM">
        <title>New Message</title>

        <para role="TEXT">Create a message from scratch and optionally send it to the
        bank. You can alternatively save it as a template, from which such
        messages can be created.</para>

        <para role="TEXT">This function displays an input form for entering the text of
        the message. You use this form to create your message and save it as a
        draft, submit it to the bank (if you have sufficient authority), or
        save it as a template.</para>

        <para role="TEXT">Use this function for all types of message except requests for
        cheque books and requests to arrange fixed term depositis. These have
        their own functions, described in the next two sections.</para>
      </section>

      <section role="ITEM">
        <title>Order Cheque Book</title>

        <para role="TEXT">Create a request for one or more cheque books from scratch and
        optionally send it to the bank. You can alternatively save it as a
        template, from which such requests can be created.</para>

        <para role="TEXT">This function displays an input form for entering the text of
        the request. You use this form to create your request and save it as a
        draft, submit it to the bank (if you have sufficient authority), or
        save it as a template.</para>
      </section>

     <section role="ITEM">
        <title>Fixed Term Deposit</title>

        <para role="TEXT">Create a message arranging a fixed term deposit, and optionally
        send it to the bank. You can alternatively save it as a template, from
        which such messages can be created.</para>

        <para role="TEXT">This function displays an input form for entering the text of
        the message. You use this form to create your message and save it as a
        draft, submit it to the bank (if you have sufficient authority), or
        save it as a template.</para>
      </section>

      <section role="ITEM">
        <title>Retrieve Draft</title>

        <para role="TEXT">As described in chapter <emphasis>Functions</emphasis>.</para>
      </section>

      <section role="ITEM">
        <title>Retrieve Unsigned</title>

        <para role="TEXT">As described in chapter <emphasis>Functions</emphasis>.</para>
      </section>
    </section>

